Detailed Description

The file implements the dual core port for the mmWave control module.

Typedef Documentation

typedef struct MMWave_Dualcore_t MMWave_Dualcore

mmWave Dual Core

The structure is used to keep track of information required for the mmWave Dual Core SOC.

typedef struct MMWave_Msg_t MMWave_Msg

mmWave Message

Messages exchanged between the mmWave execution domains have a payload identifier which is used to describe the contents of the actual message

typedef struct MMWave_MsgEvent_t MMWave_MsgEvent

mmWave Message for event

The structure defines the message which is used to exchange asynchronus events generated by the BSS between the mmWave execution domains.

typedef struct MMWave_MsgHeader_t MMWave_MsgHeader

mmWave Message Header

Messages exchanged between the mmWave execution domains have a fixed size header added to all the messages which are exchanged.

typedef enum MMWave_PayloadId_e MMWave_PayloadId

mmWave Payload identifier

Messages exchanged between the mmWave execution domains have a payload identifier which is used to describe the contents of the actual message

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum MMWave_PayloadId_e

mmWave Payload identifier

Messages exchanged between the mmWave execution domains have a payload identifier which is used to describe the contents of the actual message

Enumerator
MMWave_PayloadId_CONFIG 

Identifier which indicates that an mmWave link configuration is being exchanged between the mmWave domains.

MMWave_PayloadId_OPEN 

Identifier which indicates that the mmWave module has been opened.

MMWave_PayloadId_CLOSE 

Identifier which indicates that the mmWave module has been closed.

MMWave_PayloadId_START 

Identifier which indicates that the mmWave link has been started and is operational.

MMWave_PayloadId_STOP 

Identifier which indicates that the mmWave link has been stopped and is no longer operational.

MMWave_PayloadId_EVENT 

Identifier which indicates that the mmWave link has reported an asynchronous event.

int32_t MMWave_deviceCfgAsyncEvent ( const MMWave_MCB *  ptrMMWaveMCB,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to configure the asynchronous events. On Dual core either the DSS or the MSS could be configured to be the recepient of asynchronous events. It also configures if the start/stop asynchronous events are enabled or disabled.

Parameters
[in]ptrMMWaveMCBPointer to the mmWave control block
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

static uint32_t MMWave_serializeCfg ( const MMWave_MCB *  ptrMMWaveMCB,
MMWave_CtrlCfg *  ptrControlCfg,
MMWave_Msg *  ptrMessage 
)
static

Description
The function is used to the serialize the control configuration into a message which can be sent to the remote mmWave peer. Serialization of the message would require that all lists (profile, chirp, BPM cfg) are placed inline into the message.

Parameters
[in]ptrMMWaveMCBPointer to the mmWave control module
[in]ptrControlCfgPointer to the control configuration which is to be sent across
[in]ptrMessagePointer to the serialized message populated by the API
Return values
Sizeof the serialized message
